"{\"uid\": \"mondaq.com-unitedstates-employee-rights-labour-relations-1501770-2024-summer-olympics-series-australia\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The 2024 Summer Olympic Games began Friday, July 26.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To\\r celebrate this international event, Littler offices around the\\r globe will share key changes in labor and employment laws that have\\r transpired since the last time their countries hosted the Olympic\\r games.1  The last time that Australia hosted the Olympics was in 2000 in\\r Sydney.\", \"from\": 53, \"to\": 338, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 285, \"end\": 294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\", \"score\": 0.6732478855037166, \"rank\": 0.48533700815093234, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 331, \"end\": 337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.999713164417807, \"rank\": 0.000284025364866432, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At that time, the Workplace Relations Act 1996 (Cth) was in\\r place.\", \"from\": 339, \"to\": 406, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That Act was repealed following the election of a Labor\\r Government in 2007, after 11 years of a Liberal (conservative)\\r government in Australia.\", \"from\": 407, \"to\": 552, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 542, \"end\": 551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\", \"score\": 0.6732478855037166, \"rank\": 0.48533700815093234, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With the repeal of the Workplace Relations\\r Act 1996 (Cth) came the introduction of theFair Work Act(FW Act),\\r which today remains the primary Commonwealth legislation regulating\\r employment and workplace relations.\", \"from\": 553, \"to\": 768, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 696, \"end\": 708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"score\": 0.9999999982237568, \"rank\": 1.1989192998319103e-09, \"text\": \"Commonwealth\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most provisions of the FW Act\\r took effect on July 1, 2009.\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 828, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The introduction of the FW Act was one of the most significant\\r reforms to Australia's employment laws in the country's\\r history and (among other things) saw the introduction of the\\r statutory modern award system.\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 1043, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 905, \"end\": 914, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\", \"score\": 0.6732478855037166, \"rank\": 0.48533700815093234, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The FW Act establishes a safety net\\r comprising: the National Employment Standards (NES), modern awards\\r and national minimum wage orders, and a compliance and enforcement\\r regime.\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1097, \"end\": 1126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Employment_Standards\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National Employment Standards\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Employment_Standards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Employment_Standards\"}, {\"begin\": 1128, \"end\": 1131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nintendo_Entertainment_System\", \"score\": 0.9999855941797164, \"rank\": 1.4405778813718811e-05, \"text\": \"NES\", \"types\": [\"Q1067263\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nintendo_Entertainment_System\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nintendo_Entertainment_System\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A modern award (award) is a legal document that sets out the\\r minimum terms and conditions of employment on top of the NES.\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1349, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1345, \"end\": 1348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nintendo_Entertainment_System\", \"score\": 0.9999855941797164, \"rank\": 1.4405778813718811e-05, \"text\": \"NES\", \"types\": [\"Q1067263\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nintendo_Entertainment_System\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nintendo_Entertainment_System\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Modern awards came into effect on January 1, 2010.\", \"from\": 1351, \"to\": 1401, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Awards provide\\r entitlements including pay, hours of work, rosters, breaks,\\r allowances, penalty, rates, and overtime.\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1520, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Modern awards are\\r industry- or occupation-based and apply to employers and employees\\r who perform work covered by the award.\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1646, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are more than 100\\r industry or occupation awards that cover most people who work in\\r Australia.\", \"from\": 1647, \"to\": 1748, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1738, \"end\": 1747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\", \"score\": 0.6732478855037166, \"rank\": 0.48533700815093234, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An employer can be covered by more than one award,\\r depending on the jobs the employees do.\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1840, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Since the introduction of the modern award system, there have\\r been significant amendments to the industry and occupation awards\\r that are in effect and apply to a significant number of Australian\\r employers.\", \"from\": 1842, \"to\": 2050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2028, \"end\": 2038, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2309438207551657e-14, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, in this Olympic year we are set to see yet\\r another significant reform with the pending introduction of\\r criminal penalties for modern award breaches.\", \"from\": 2051, \"to\": 2210, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"TheFair Work Legislation Amendment (Closing Loopholes) Act\\r 2023introduces a number of workplace changes, some of which\\r have already taken effect as of late 2023 and during the first half\\r of 2024.\", \"from\": 2212, \"to\": 2410, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Further amendments will apply from August 2024 or in early\\r 2025, including amendments addressing the following:  One of the most noteworthy upcoming changes is the criminalizing\\r of wage underpayments.\", \"from\": 2411, \"to\": 2613, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This means intentional underpayment of wages\\r by employers will become a criminal offence in certain\\r circumstances.\", \"from\": 2614, \"to\": 2730, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Employers will commit an offence if:  The wage theft offence will carry a maximum of 10 years'\\r imprisonment, and/or a maximum fine of the greater of:  Another noteworthy change for employers to be aware of in this\\r Olympic year is the new right to disconnect law, which is a mere\\r two months away from implementation.\", \"from\": 2731, \"to\": 3049, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The new law will provide\\r eligible employees with the right to refuse employer or third-party\\r contact (including attempted contact) outside of working hours\\r unless that refusal is unreasonable.\", \"from\": 3050, \"to\": 3245, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In determining whether an\\r employee's refusal is unreasonable, several factors will be\\r considered, including but not limited to:  In the event of a dispute, if the employer and the employee are\\r unable to resolve it after discussion, either party can go to theFair Work\\r Commission(the Australian national workplace relations\\r tribunal) for dispute resolution.\", \"from\": 3246, \"to\": 3607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3533, \"end\": 3543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2309438207551657e-14, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All modern awards will include a right to disconnect term by\\r August 26, 2024, adding specific rules to awards to ensure the new\\r terms reflect the realities of the occupation and industry.\", \"from\": 3609, \"to\": 3798, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We recommend that employers act promptly to review their pay\\r practices, policies, and employment agreements to comply with the\\r new laws ahead of August.\", \"from\": 3800, \"to\": 3954, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Footnote  1.\", \"from\": 3956, \"to\": 3968, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Littler's International Guide discusses more than\\r 90 workplace law topics in over 45 countries/territories, including\\r jurisdictions in every region of the world.\", \"from\": 3969, \"to\": 4132, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For more information on\\r the International Guide, please contact your Littler attorney or KM\\r - Managing Editor/PublicationsKristen Countryman.\", \"from\": 4133, \"to\": 4276, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4223, \"end\": 4225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Knowledge_management\", \"score\": 0.9999999997044142, \"rank\": 2.943707266960349e-10, \"text\": \"KM\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Knowledge_management\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Knowledge_management\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In\\r addition, Littler's Global Guide Quarterly (GGQ) provides\\r high\\u2010level notice of recent global labor and employment law\\r developments in key countries in the American, EMEA, and APAC\\r regions.Click hereto subscribe to the GGQ.\", \"from\": 4277, \"to\": 4506, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4438, \"end\": 4446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999956958163, \"rank\": 3.142527594307485e-09, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4448, \"end\": 4452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Medicines_Agency\", \"score\": 0.9999999987080628, \"rank\": 1.2918794119853223e-09, \"text\": \"EMEA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Medicines_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Medicines_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 4458, \"end\": 4462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asia-Pacific\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"APAC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asia-Pacific\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asia-Pacific\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The content of this article is intended to provide a general\\r guide to the subject matter.\", \"from\": 4508, \"to\": 4598, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Specialist advice should be sought\\r about your specific circumstances.\", \"from\": 4599, \"to\": 4669, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Connecting Knowledge & People  POWERED BYMONDAQ AI  \\u00a9 Mondaq\\u00ae Ltd  1994 - 2025.\", \"from\": 4671, \"to\": 4750, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All Rights Reserved  Mondaq uses cookies on this website.\", \"from\": 4751, \"to\": 4808, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4772, \"end\": 4778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondaq\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mondaq\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondaq\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondaq\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By using our website you agree to our use of cookies as set out in our Privacy Policy.\", \"from\": 4809, \"to\": 4895, \"entities\": []}]}"